article.headline: Northwestern 76, Chicago St 60
article.story: EVANSTON, Ill. (AP) -- Jitim Young scored 23 points and had 10 rebounds as Northwestern defeated Chicago State 76-60 on Sunday night. Young was a perfect 7-for-7 from the floor, made both of his two shots from 3-point range and hit all but one of his eight free throw attempts. Vedran Vukusic added 11 points and Davor Duvancic and T.J. Parker each had 10 for the Wildcats (1-1) Young had 14 points on 4-for-4 shooting in the first half as Northwestern took a 39-29 lead into halftime. Chicago State was led by Tony Weeden, who scored 14 of his gme-high 24 points in the first half. The Cougars cut Northwestern's lead to 59-49 on a Leon Petty basket with 6:38 left, but the Wildcats answered with an 8-0 run to extend the lead to 67-49. Craig Franklin added 11 points for Chicago State (0-2), which lost on an opponent's home court for the 34th straight time.
